# 2-Week Prototype Build Plan (Godot-First)

## Milestone 0 (Day 1): Godot Setup — Start Here
- Install Godot (current stable)
- Create project and scene structure (`Main`, `Court`, `Player`, `Ball`, `UI`)
- Add keyboard input map (move, hit timing, shot modifiers)
- Add placeholder sprites/shapes

**Deliverable:** controllable player, visible court, spawned ball.

## Milestone 1 (Days 2–4): Rally Core
- Ball movement and bounce logic
- Hit timing windows (early/perfect/late)
- Flat/topspin/slice variation behaviors
- Baseline lob input condition
- Basic CPU return logic

**Deliverable:** playable rallies with shot variety.

## Milestone 2 (Days 5–7): Match Rules
- Serve state machine (flat/topspin/slice)
- Point tracking and game progression
- End-of-match and rematch flow
- Build first Exhibition mode loop

**Deliverable:** complete 1vCPU exhibition match.

## Milestone 3 (Days 8–10): Difficulty + Personalities
- Add 5 difficulty levels
- Add light rubber-band tuning
- Give opponents distinct tendencies (e.g., safer vs aggressive)
- Tuning pass for 3–5 minute match target

**Deliverable:** difficulty ladder that feels different and fun.

## Milestone 4 (Days 11–12): Tournament + Presentation
- Add simple tournament bracket/progression
- Add menu screens and readable retro UI text
- Add placeholder chiptune/SFX mix

**Deliverable:** prototype with exhibition + tournament modes.

## Milestone 5 (Days 13–14): Stabilize
- Bug fixes and feel polish
- Performance/readability pass
- Final scope trim if needed

**Deliverable:** stable, fun prototype ready for your next iteration.

